               <head>Ziḳne Yehudah by Leone Modena</head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>A collection of responses. </summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="he"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="107v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ziḳne Yehudah</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">זקני יהודה</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="viaf.org/viaf/4948231">Modena, Leone</persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf.org/viaf/4948231">מודנה, יהודה אריה בן יצחק</persName>
                     
                     
                     
                     </author>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>131 responses. Folios 76r-84v contain diplomas granted by the author to a considerable number of younger contemporaries. Folio 86r cintains a similar document signed Menahem Azariah (of Fano) and endorsed by Yehudah Aryeh in 1606. Folios 86v and 87r contain two letters. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Folios 103v-105r contain an index (incomplete) to the responses in the volume, and folios 106r-108r described the contents of two other volumes of responses in possession of the author (32 and 20 entries respectively). </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
               
               
               
